Magyar Telekom, PZU May Move: Central European Equity Preview

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 
2011-06-01T06:25:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/telekom-pzu-may-move-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index gained 1.1 percent, the Czech PX Index
climbed 0.9 percent and  Hungary ’s BUX Index jumped 2.6 percent.  Magyar Telekom Nyrt. (MTEL HB): Hungary’s former phone
monopoly, controlled by Deutsche Telekom AG, said that the
Budapest Metropolitan Court of Appeal upheld a first-instance
decision confirming the validity of decisions at the 2010 annual
meeting are valid, rejecting a challenge from minority
shareholders. The shares gained 2.1 percent to 546 forint.  PZU SA (PZU PW): Shareholders of Poland’s biggest insurer
will vote on the government’s proposal to cap other owners’
voting rights at 10 percent. The government owns a 45 percent
stake in PZU.  Separately, PZU had its share-price estimate increased to
449 zloty from 431 zloty at Citigroup Inc., and raised to 444
zloty from 436 zloty at Morgan Stanley. PZU shares rose less
than 0.1 percent to 389 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
